# Why this is the right behavior

Because CFT is path-sensitive:

* `failed/...` ❌
* `retrying/...` ❌
* `outgoing_e-invoicing/...` ✅

So retry must call CFT only with:

```text
outgoing_e-invoicing/<filename>.zip.pgp
```

And because you want failed files preserved on retry failure, **copy** is better than move.

